 <i>de Werdon</i>, mentioned in 1280, as having his name from Verdun (Manche, France); see   Verdon  ."]},{"name":"Verdun","meanings":["French: habitational name from any of several places in France called Verdun. The placename is probably of Gaulish origin, deriving from <i>ver(n)</i> ‘alder’ + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill, fortress’.","Spanish and Catalan: habitational name from Verdú in Catalonia (Spain), which has the same origin as the French name (see 1 above).","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Verdon  , a cognate of 1 above. This surname is very rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Alicia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Modern Latinate form of   Alice .  It was borne by the British ballerina  Alicia Markova  (born  Lilian Alicia Marks ,  1910–2004 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Alisha","meanings":["Modern Latinate form of   Alice .  It was borne by the British ballerina  Alicia Markova  (born  Lilian Alicia Marks ,  1910–2004 )."]},{"name":"Alisia","meanings":["Modern Latinate form of   Alice .  It was borne by the British ballerina  Alicia Markova  (born  Lilian Alicia Marks ,  1910–2004 )."]},{"name":"Alyssa","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alissa ."]},{"name":"Alissa","meanings":["Contracted form of   Alicia ."]},{"name":"Alesha","meanings":["Respelling of   Alicia ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Alicia de Verdon was born as the daughter of Sir Norman de Verdun of Farnham Royal and  Alton and Lesceline de Clinton. She had at least 2 sons with Ivo Pantulf. She died about 1291."},"et":{"–Abt 1291":"–umbes 1291","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1142–1177":"1142–1177","1150–1192":"1150–1192","–1291":"–1291","1106–Male":"1106–Surnud","1126–1166":"1126–1166","1145–Male":"1145–Surnud","1107–1166":"1107–1166","1124–1207":"1124–1207","after 2